  "title": "BIM MODELLER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Responsibilities</p><p>· Develop and maintain detailed BIM models based on project specifications and design documentation</p><p>· Collaborate with architects, engineers, and other stakeholders to ensure model accuracy and consistency</p><p>· Conduct clash detection and resolution to minimize conflicts during the construction phase</p><p>·  Prepare and present 3D visualizations and simulations for project stakeholders</p><p>·  Assist in the development of BIM execution plans and standards</p><p>·  Stay updated on industry trends and advancements in BIM technology and software</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>· Diploma/Degree in Civil / Structural / Architecture or equivalent.</p><p>· Possess BIM certificate</p><p>· Minimum 2 years experience in AutoCad Drafting & Autodesk Revit Modelling</p><p>· Can read & understand working drawings (architecture, structural and M & E)</p><p>• Capable of working independently with strong self-motivation.</p><p>• Skilled in producing BIM documentation, modelling, coordination, and drawings.<br /><br />• Proven track record with at least 2 years of hands-on BIM (Autodesk Revit) experience.</p><p>Other Information</p><ul><li>Working days: 5.5 days</li></ul><ul><li>Salary: to be discuss (salary will commensurate according to experience &qualifications)</li></ul><p><br />Please Indicate The Below Information In Your Resume</p><p>• Current & Expected Salary</p><p>• Reason(s) for leaving</p><p>• Notice Period / Availability to commence work</p>",
